Subject: Allotment (26th Oct - 11am)

Body:
Hi all,

In continuation to the discussion had on 22nd Oct (Saturday) on subject implementation. Phase-wise implementation will happen to ensure smooth rollout.

Phase I - Week 43  (24th Oct  29th Oct)
1) Since there are some showstoppers on confirm activity task in PTS Kumar Sir, will modify PTS to capture both WIP hours and actual manual hours by Friday (28th
October). Currently the actual hours should be 8 hours to close the confirm activity task, if the actual hour update is deactivated it will not be possible to close the task
2) Trial run will happen this week to capture the possible issues faced
3) All tickets thru any format (Mail, chat, calls) will be recorded in PTS and monitored by the heads
4)Team heads will follow-up with the team members on usage of WIP
5) Weekly allotment report will be send on daily basis
Phase II  Week 44 (31st Oct  5th Nov)
1) Dual run  Both WIP hours and manual actual hours will be captured in PTS
2) Leads will evaluate the difference in gap between the actual hours and the manual hours on daily basis
3) Regular Feebdack and coaching will be given to the Team members 
Phase III  Week 45 (7th Nov  12th Nov)
1) Based on the outcome of Phase II, the manual hours update in PTS will be disabled 
2) Kumar, will do the necessary changes in PTS to disable the manual hours updated 
3)  Go Live will be on Week 45 (10 th Nov)
Please approach self if need any clarifications

Regards

Stephen

Second Line Beach,Parrys,

Body:
Dear Ranjith,

We find that the print option in USD is not giving the correct amounts. Earlier we have been sending USD invoices to our customers with this option & had no issues with the amounts. Mujeebuddin
forwarded the invoice to our customer & they have come up with an adverse mail against ALTA (customer mail attached). Invoice details in screenshot below.

This is a very bad remark for ALTA because of the system issues we are facing. We cannot provide a timely service to our customer, ending up with an excuse that there is a software or system
issue. 
Please ensure a good service from your end. Its more than a year we are using the system & we are still facing daily issues & getting the same issues rectified again & again.

Regards,
Sindhu

Body:
Good Morning all
RIC  Subhranshu , please issue the tickets 

Meeting with in regards to

Centralized payment process in EBMSAuto -seamless flow in Books of Accounts from Liner/FFD/ Flexi module

Concall was held amongst Rajna Mam, Rajeev, Subhranshu & Mujib (EBMS), in relation above processes to be set in EBMS 

Following is concluded as below

1.Auto seamless flow from ops (Liner : Vasco & GMLLC/FFD/Flexi module) to FAS

Invoice

Here , primary check will be Invoice print , when invoice print is triggered of the FINAL INVOICE , the auto posting in accounts will be effected.The posting will be real time and automated totally only for transactions which are clear viz : Customer & charges are mapped with FAS.If the invoice is created for which customer or charges is not mapped, alert will be sent to designated users , but system will also to generate invoice.

This will collate in the existing posting module. Once the F&A HO team does the necessary mapping /approval of customer & Charge code into
FAS , the invoice will be appear for posting and the accounts user will have this posted using the Invoice/credit note/receipt posting module to FAS

Credit Notes
 Credit notes will be automatically posted to FAS from Accounts . 
 There should be approver concept . When a user issue credit notes , it should be approved by Approver(HOD/BM/anointed user) and then
only the credit note should be allowed to be generated /taken 
print and posted to FAS
. The Credit note Report in operation should shows /capture all the log from request of credit note to approval to issuance /posting.

Receipts : 
 Receipts will be auto posted from all these ops module to Accounts.
 Ebms to give master table where in Goodrich HO defines location wise/module wise cash and bank ledgers
 By default this bank details will be fetched at time of receipt generation. 

For New forwarding module , this feature is already be asked for in GAP itself , it is part of package , NO ENHANCEMENT. 

Tickets for auto posting needs to raised by ERP team one each for each module.

2. Centralized Bank Payment Process

All payments /designated payments will be centralized from HO.

The purchase bills will be booked at branches as the existing practice.For bills will be settled from HO , Branch user will selecting the same and scheduling it .The HO Disbursement Bank account will be selected at HO .Table/interface/Master for the same to be with Goodrich. These bills can be seen by the anointed HO users for payments ( Table /master/interface providing rights should be with Goodrich)HO user selects these invoices of various branches (but one vendor) and makes the payment . Proper & intelligent payment interface should be provided
by EBMS teamThere will one Branch wise Control account for accounting purposeIn case of branch control account entries for centralised payment, same has to be auto created and posted .HO team will only select the invoices popping
up for payment.Entry will be :-

IN HO BOOKS (MANUAL PAYMENT ENTRY THROUGH THE INTERFACE PROVIDED )
Dr Branch control Account
Cr Bank

IN BRANCH BOOKS (AUTOMATED & LINKED TO HO PAYMENT ENTRY)
 Dr Vendor /Customer 
 Cr Branch Control Account

Ticket for Centralized bank process to provided by ERP Team

Tentative completion date to satisfaction of the Goodrich user will be on or before 15th of August 2019

Body:
DearUdhay,
          As discussed withyou, As per New voyage schedule we need to require changes in Container Status EDI (ETA,DDD and ATA).These EDI based on old voyage schedule according to new voyage schedule we need to pick data as per new voyage.

For your reference :Issue id E430 Successfully Inserted

ETA EDI :-

EstimatedTimeOfArrival --> Take data from Tracking For Carrier Booking Process (ETA DESTINATION Field)

StatusDate --> Take data from Tracking For Carrier Booking Process (ETA DESTINATION Field)

ATA EDI :-

EstimatedTimeOfArrival --> Take data from Tracking For Carrier Booking Process (ETA DESTINATION Field)

StatusDate --> Take data from Tracking For Carrier Booking Process (ETA DESTINATION Field)

ActualTimeOfArrival --> Take data from Tracking For Carrier Booking Process (ETA DESTINATION Field)

DDD EDI :-

EstimatedTimeOfArrival --> Take data from Tracking For Carrier Booking Process (ETA DESTINATION Field)

StatusLocationPlace --> Depot Address (SPS Depot)

StatusLocationCode --> Depot Address (INNSA)

-- 

Thanks & Regards

Good day.

We understood, the loop hole which was filled early on this week by you.
But we are not getting, what about the SBK which are still posted against the deleted VDB.

Because as per you while VDB deletion system was checking only for PBK.
So, user will delete the PBK 1st & delete the VDB.

But as per the practice & observation from the day one of Feeder Bill execution, system wont allow to delete VDB without SBK & PBK delete.
We dont know from when the check got removed.
Here the SBK may or may not be deleted by user, because the check was removed in system.

So, give us the list of SBK which are still hanging in FAS without the VDB.

Also same VDB number should not generate in system.
Hope the number generation logic having the counter to increase the VDB number.

At least system should check Bill number in Feeder bill Booking & Bill number which already Stored SBK, then this type of situation not occurred while creation of VDB.

Dear Subhranshu,

Please ref. to our discussion. Despite repeatedly informing / intimating that the invoice calculation or DO validity
should start from ATA (Berthing date) updated in the voyage master. We have noticed that still system is calculating basis ETA. ETA is nothing but expected or estimated date of arrival & not the actual one. It can be any date

We have generated a storage invoice wherein the amount is less than the invoice amount raised by the terminal (invoice
attached). Terminals calculation starts from 06.09.2019 (basis ATA  terminal gives 2 days free ) whereas our invoice calculation starts from 07.09.2019 ( basis ETA ). It is because of the mismatch of GLD date  system is not calculating basis berthing date.
If system calculation is on the basis of ETA, then we will be losing one day storage charges i.e. loss of revenue to the company.

As per Inventory department the Budget Monthly head is wrong. 
Now its taking the data from Agent Forecast Update. But it should take the data from MRG.

As per Trade, same the Budget Monthly should take the data from MRG.
And the column Total Inventory should show the colour codes of surplus & deficit instead of the column Balance To Perform basis some logic/condition.

Please find below the logic for the surplus / deficit colour code for Total Inventory.

Surplus

Balanced

Deficit

Surplus

If the Inventory (Empty + import Laden ) is more than 2 times of Volume Balance to perform against the Budget 

Balanced

If the Inventory (Empty + import Laden ) is More than 1 times and less than 2 times of Volume Balance to perform against the Budget 

Deficit

If the inventory (Empty + import Laden ) is less than 1 times of Volume Balance to perform against the Budget

Dear Ranjith and Udhay

Good Day.

Ref to our last week discussion on subject issue.

Pls note the following :-

1) Other Invoice option suggest by Ranjith is not workable in the said case, as same is not linked to finance module of STOLT.

2) Hence we need option to raise invoice in Export DISB and SUPPL Invoice against those Export shipment against which customer
  has rejected tank at time of stuffing and same was return back to empty depot and all additional operation charges has to be
  billed to respective vendor ( Depot/Transporter etc).

3) We will update Movement register as under :-

    Note :- Hence rejected tank will remain in batch and system will allow user to raise Export DISB and SUPPL Invoice against
          rejected tank to concern vendor ( Depot/Transporter etc).Pls check and advise on possibility to use above logic.

 b) Being Tank return to depot, hence system will not show said tank in underloading report and after next AV move system should
   allow the tank to link to another export or repo batch, Pls check and advise on possibility to use above logic.

Awaiting for your early response.

Dear Mr.Ranjith

Well noted your email below, however as understand our HO mumbai Team cannot solve the Ebms technical issues therefore its always addressed to EBMS team directly and cc to HO Mumbai as was suggested earlier. Further we Do not want
to waste time in going up and down on the emails and the issues therefore is addressed directly to the Ebms team. Please discussfurther with Anand and Sushant on same and if can find something more proactive solution.

Further Please note 1 main criteriaand the difference between CCU and other locations............
1. We are handling Ebms for WHL fully and also for the NVO's...........
2. WHL Volume of Cntrs / BL's are approx Avg 65/70 BL's IMPORT and same 65/70 BL's EXPORT per vessel per week.
3. Vessel arrival is weekly and When Import Dept works Export dept also starts working for Export leg and SI updates / Invoice generation etc etc.
4. We have at a time approx 3 Imports and 3 Exports Docs person+ 2 Customer Service person working on the EBMS ...... SAME time .....
5. Further Sales 2 person for WHL also works on the EBMS may be same time... Total approx 10 person in one go.......
6. If any NVO booking then additional 2 more may be added in the system.
7. Further have left Operation atleast 1-2 person also do there updating the Cntrs status.......daily

The above is the difference ... number of user working at one go in the System..... therefore please DO NOT compare with other location where feel the number of user may be much less at a time.

DO PLEASE LOOK INTO THE ISSUES SERIOUSLY AND PROMPTLY AND TRY TO SOLVE SAME ASAP AS THIS HAS BEEN REGULAR PROBLEM OF CCU.

Further on the pointed issues please note flwg update......

1. System slowness ----- Still the problem not sorted.
2. Menu Acess - Agin system slowness still the problem
3. EDI file - Matching and uploading not Sorted till date...... Still the problem

of Deleting since both HAZ docs and NON HAZ docs coming togather which should not be case ---- only one applicable at one time.
Please check with my Docs Team (Parimal and Prasun) for further details.
7. IN export Docs I had asked to insert the Container detention charges auto input from the System of Cntrs inventory update / management .......
Same is missing and not done till date.

Await your further prompt feedbcak on same and sort the issues asap.

Body:
DearRanjith,
           Due to load on New More Request we need to minimize the data from screen.Please find the criteria below in more request screen check at yourend if have challengesto you please let me know.

1) STOLT Move is only 8 Numbers, EBMS system should allow on Minimum 8 Number to Maximum 12 Numbers to be updated in New Move request in EBMS system.

2) If Move number is not updated then system should not allow user to generate any invoice to Customer or STOLT.

3) Only 1 or 2 Month New Move record Batch wise must be fetched to avoid slow down of EBMS system (Filter Criteria on Date).

4) In case if we have to change any old move as per STOLT Requirement at a later stage for accounting purpose then system should allow user to modify the same through system.
5) Only Pending New Move for updation must be fetched on top, which will assist users to track and update pending new move quickly (blank record we need to display first).

For your Reference Ticket ID : E829
--
